Limited-edition giclée print of <i>Everything Will Probably Be Alright</i> by Ben Kamprath.

Printed on <a href="http://www.epson.com/cgi-bin/Store/ProductMediaSpec.jsp?BV_UseBVCookie=yes&infoType=Overview&oid=-9823&category=Paper+%26+Media">Epson Somerset® Velvet Fine Art Paper</a> using <a href="http://www.epson.com/cgi-bin/Store/Landing/UltraChromeK3.jsp?ref=r0302EMb42&s_kwcid=TC|6812|epson%20ultrachrome||S||3762110322&gclid=CNuTwpuv-5wCFRQpawodcjjcbg">Epson UltraChrome™ inks</a>. The print measures 13"x19" and is signed by the artist.

This print is a museum-quality reproduction.

The edition is limited to 25 pieces, each print is hand-numbered and signed by the artist.

The print is also available framed. Each frame is handmade by the artist. The frame is constructed from poplar wood and is sanded down to achieve a silky smooth luster. Acrylic glass with a UV coating is used to protect the print from light damage.

<i>What is giclée? <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gicl%C3%A9e" target="_blank">Learn more...</a></i>

